1
00:00:00,810 --> 00:00:02,510
Was everything okay after I left?

2
00:00:02,510 --> 00:00:03,880
(Episode 42)

3
00:00:04,710 --> 00:00:05,710
It was fine.

4
00:00:05,980 --> 00:00:08,610
Oh Jang Mi's sister took her mother away,
so there won't be any trouble.

5
00:00:09,480 --> 00:00:11,080
Things seem quiet so far.

6
00:00:11,420 --> 00:00:13,050
I heard Jung Suk Hee's mind had regressed,

7
00:00:13,550 --> 00:00:15,490
but do you think she might be remembering
what happened?

8
00:00:16,150 --> 00:00:17,320
Who knows?

9
00:00:17,620 --> 00:00:19,360
I was on pins and needles earlier.

10
00:00:19,720 --> 00:00:22,830
I really thought she was about to spill
everything we did.

11
00:00:22,930 --> 00:00:24,330
"Everything we did?"

12
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:26,260
What on earth did they do?

13
00:00:26,830 --> 00:00:30,640
Mom, what in the world did you do
to Oh Jang Mi's mother?

14
00:00:30,940 --> 00:00:33,570
Anyway, we dodged a bullet this time,

15
00:00:33,710 --> 00:00:36,240
but I have no idea
what's going to happen next.

16
00:00:37,040 --> 00:00:38,610
They're like roaches.

17
00:00:38,610 --> 00:00:40,810
Just when I think I've gotten rid of them,
they crawl back out.

18
00:00:41,810 --> 00:00:43,720
I can never let my guard down.

19
00:00:45,550 --> 00:00:47,590
If I have to see Oh Jang Mi again,
you stay away.

20
00:00:48,620 --> 00:00:50,590
- Understood.
- Then again,

21
00:00:51,190 --> 00:00:53,490
the best thing would be
to avoid seeing her altogether.

22
00:00:54,090 --> 00:00:58,060
Please, deal with her for good this time
so she never sees the light of day again.

23
00:01:03,670 --> 00:01:04,800
My own mother...

24
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,040
Is this the kind of person she is?

25
00:01:35,570 --> 00:01:38,000
You're still here?

26
00:01:40,670 --> 00:01:43,310
I was just about to leave.

27
00:01:44,010 --> 00:01:45,610
Are you heading home, Lawyer Kang?

28
00:01:45,710 --> 00:01:49,550
No. Jang Mi hasn't been eating,
so I'm going to get her some porridge.

29
00:01:49,650 --> 00:01:51,780
You're going to such trouble, Lawyer Kang.

30
00:01:52,150 --> 00:01:55,090
Please take good care of Oh Jang Mi,
Lawyer Kang.

31
00:01:55,420 --> 00:01:57,090
She must be so heartbroken.

32
00:01:57,360 --> 00:01:58,490
You don't have to worry.

33
00:02:26,950 --> 00:02:27,990
What was that?

34
00:02:29,090 --> 00:02:30,620
Who on earth is Mom?

35
00:02:31,490 --> 00:02:32,490
Who is she really?

36
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:42,300
Looks like Seo Rin isn't feeling well.
She's just lying in bed under the covers.

37
00:02:42,370 --> 00:02:45,070
Is my little girl feeling sick?

38
00:02:45,140 --> 00:02:47,510
Well, she still has to eat breakfast.

39
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,870
You know what they say,

40
00:02:48,870 --> 00:02:50,480
even a ghost looks better
with a full stomach.

41
00:02:51,440 --> 00:02:54,810
- Mom!
- Can't you read the room at all?

42
00:02:55,350 --> 00:02:57,350
Do you just say
whatever pops into your head?

43
00:02:57,980 --> 00:02:58,980
What's your problem?

44
00:02:59,380 --> 00:03:01,120
It's just a saying.

45
00:03:01,120 --> 00:03:03,590
Why are you jumping down
my throat this early in the morning?

46
00:03:03,590 --> 00:03:05,660
Didn't you hear that Seo Rin is sick?

47
00:03:06,220 --> 00:03:08,090
How could you say something like that
at a time like this?

48
00:03:09,790 --> 00:03:13,060
It's not like Seo Rin is on her deathbed
or has some fatal disease.

49
00:03:13,130 --> 00:03:15,430
- Why are you policing every word I say?
- All right, that's enough.

50
00:03:15,900 --> 00:03:18,100
Why are you all arguing
at the breakfast table?

51
00:03:26,810 --> 00:03:27,810
First,

52
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:30,580
I need to get a DNA test to be certain.

53
00:03:31,350 --> 00:03:33,920
I need to know if Oh Jang Mi and I
are actually twins...

54
00:03:34,420 --> 00:03:36,650
and if my mom
is really my biological mother.

55
00:03:38,160 --> 00:03:40,860
But why would Mom want to kill Oh Jang Mi?

56
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:44,700
I'm so scared.

57
00:03:46,060 --> 00:03:48,370
I can't even stand the sight of her face.

58
00:03:55,810 --> 00:03:57,380
Lawyer Kang, come on in.

59
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:02,750
Is Jang Mi still not well?

60
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,420
As if she's the only one to lose a dad.

61
00:04:04,650 --> 00:04:06,220
I lost my dad too, you know.

62
00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:10,250
If she just lies there, will someone come
and spoon-feed her?

63
00:04:10,360 --> 00:04:13,260
She hasn't accepted his death yet.

64
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:15,830
Please, just give her some time.

65
00:04:16,890 --> 00:04:18,500
He was my dad, too!

66
00:04:19,730 --> 00:04:21,670
It's not like I can believe it either.

67
00:04:21,970 --> 00:04:24,070
But we still have to get by.
What choice do we have?

68
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:27,040
We have to open the store and earn money
to put food on the table.

69
00:04:42,290 --> 00:04:45,160
Jang Mi, please get up
and have some porridge.

70
00:04:46,890 --> 00:04:49,230
I said we should not see each other.
Why are you here?

71
00:04:49,460 --> 00:04:52,360
Eat this. Then we can go
to the police station together.

72
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:56,070
Did you get a call from Detective Kim?

73
00:04:57,000 --> 00:04:58,470
Did he say why my dad was there?

74
00:04:59,070 --> 00:05:01,270
What car did he take? Who was he with?

75
00:05:01,270 --> 00:05:02,740
And why was he drinking? Tell me.

76
00:05:02,810 --> 00:05:04,080
I'll tell you after you eat.

77
00:05:05,340 --> 00:05:06,340
Here you go.

78
00:05:07,180 --> 00:05:08,980
Please, just tell me now.

79
00:05:09,310 --> 00:05:10,680
Have you looked in the mirror today?

80
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,720
The mirror? Why?

81
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:15,690
Because you look like you could collapse
at any second.

82
00:05:17,220 --> 00:05:18,260
Here.

83
00:05:19,290 --> 00:05:23,190
You need to eat and get your strength back
to find the truth about your father.

84
00:05:24,860 --> 00:05:26,630
Fine. I'll eat.

85
00:05:27,330 --> 00:05:30,870
Your father would want you
to keep your strength up.

86
00:05:35,570 --> 00:05:36,610
I...

87
00:05:37,410 --> 00:05:39,810
I made a promise to your father
in front of his portrait.

88
00:05:40,980 --> 00:05:42,280
That I'd protect...

89
00:05:42,950 --> 00:05:46,280
you and your mother,
Tae Pyung, and Tae Sook.

90
00:05:48,790 --> 00:05:50,860
To make up for everything
my father did wrong,

91
00:05:52,290 --> 00:05:53,620
I swear I'll protect you.

92
00:05:53,860 --> 00:05:56,890
What gives you the right
to make a promise like that to my dad?

93
00:05:58,360 --> 00:05:59,760
I'll protect my own family.

94
00:06:05,900 --> 00:06:07,570
"Wedding imminent."

95
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:16,250
This is the article about Dad
going missing in Monaco,

96
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:19,680
and this is a birth announcement
for a daughter.

97
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:21,790
Wait.

98
00:06:22,290 --> 00:06:26,020
But there's not a single mention
of twins in any of these newspapers.

99
00:06:27,490 --> 00:06:30,760
Jang Mi, you must be heartbroken
after losing your father.

100
00:06:31,030 --> 00:06:35,030
You shouldn't have to deal with this.
Let Manager Lee handle it.

101
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:39,470
If you think something's not right,
I'll have him look into it for you.

102
00:06:39,870 --> 00:06:42,440
That means a lot. Thank you.

103
00:06:43,370 --> 00:06:44,380
That's strange.

104
00:06:44,740 --> 00:06:47,350
Mom must know
that Oh Jang Mi and I are twins.

105
00:06:47,980 --> 00:06:49,910
Is that why she's trying
to kill Oh Jang Mi?

106
00:06:50,750 --> 00:06:53,280
Or is Mom hiding something else?

107
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:56,390
What could it be?

108
00:07:09,130 --> 00:07:10,130
Hey.

109
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:12,240
What are you doing here?

110
00:07:14,370 --> 00:07:15,610
Listen here, my dear daughter-in-law.

111
00:07:16,140 --> 00:07:20,010
With your subordinates watching,
how dare you address me so casually?

112
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,310
Watch your mouth.

113
00:07:22,980 --> 00:07:23,980
What did you just say?

114
00:07:24,420 --> 00:07:25,980
We may not be family on paper,

115
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:27,350
but in your heart,

116
00:07:27,350 --> 00:07:29,690
you should treat me as a mother-in-law.

117
00:07:30,090 --> 00:07:32,290
You're really showing
your poor upbringing.

118
00:07:32,990 --> 00:07:37,730
I came here myself to teach you a lesson
about that mouth of yours.

119
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:38,900
Are you done talking?

120
00:07:39,530 --> 00:07:42,270
How dare you barge in here
and spout that nonsense?

121
00:07:42,270 --> 00:07:44,070
I may not be his official wife,

122
00:07:44,770 --> 00:07:47,000
but it's about time...

123
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,770
you understood
that I'm the Chairman's woman.

124
00:07:50,710 --> 00:07:52,980
So accept it, my daughter-in-law. Okay?

125
00:07:54,880 --> 00:07:55,950
Unbelievable.

126
00:07:56,450 --> 00:07:58,350
That's exactly why I came.
What's it to you?

127
00:07:58,950 --> 00:07:59,950
Why, you...

128
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:02,290
Oh my goodness.

129
00:08:02,390 --> 00:08:05,220
- What was that? Don't know your place?
- Hey.

130
00:08:05,320 --> 00:08:08,760
I tried to be patient,
but you've crossed the line, haven't you?

131
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:13,330
I thought your little act was cute,
but you keep talking back, Yeom San Wol!

132
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:16,500
Let go! Let go of me!
You're the one who crossed the line!

133
00:08:16,570 --> 00:08:17,900
You humiliated me this morning,

134
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:20,970
- How dare you treat me like this?
- Don't even try me!

135
00:08:20,970 --> 00:08:23,410
- Oh my.
- I dare you to run that mouth again.

136
00:08:23,410 --> 00:08:24,880
What? Am I your daughter-in-law?

137
00:08:25,180 --> 00:08:27,810
Let go! Let go of me now!

138
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:29,810
You savage! I'm your mother-in-law.

139
00:08:29,810 --> 00:08:31,650
What do you think you're doing?

140
00:08:31,720 --> 00:08:36,290
Go on, try and resist.
I'll rip out every last bit of your hair.

141
00:08:36,450 --> 00:08:41,190
- Go on and resist!
- Hey, let go! That hurts.

142
00:08:41,290 --> 00:08:43,860
- Oh my. She's killing me.
- Stop that right now!

143
00:08:43,960 --> 00:08:47,800
Oh, my head hurts. Somebody help me.

144
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:49,630
Are you badly hurt?

145
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:56,540
- Father.
- What do you think you're doing?

146
00:08:57,410 --> 00:08:59,510
Where did you learn
such atrocious manners?

147
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,760
What on earth is going on?

148
00:09:11,590 --> 00:09:12,620
Does Grandpa...

149
00:09:13,190 --> 00:09:15,860
know about the twins?

150
00:09:16,360 --> 00:09:17,900
Or, is he completely in the dark?

151
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:21,800
I don't know what to do!

152
00:09:25,640 --> 00:09:28,570
Mrs. Yeom may have worked
for you in the past,

153
00:09:29,110 --> 00:09:30,510
but now she's your mother-in-law.

154
00:09:31,910 --> 00:09:33,950
- Apologize to her this instant.
- Father.

155
00:09:34,410 --> 00:09:36,410
It's not like she had
a formal wedding with you.

156
00:09:37,180 --> 00:09:38,820
I refuse to acknowledge her.

157
00:09:39,680 --> 00:09:42,850
Besides, you only told us a few days ago.
Why are you rushing this?

158
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,620
What do you mean, "rushing?"

159
00:09:45,360 --> 00:09:47,290
We've been living under one roof
like a family for ages.

160
00:09:47,860 --> 00:09:51,060
You may have ordered her around before,
but not anymore.

161
00:09:51,300 --> 00:09:54,870
You still treat her like your employee,
which makes Mrs. Yeom even more upset.

162
00:09:55,130 --> 00:09:56,830
That’s why she’s so insistent that you
treat her like your mother-in-law.

163
00:09:56,970 --> 00:09:58,470
Exactly. That's right.

164
00:09:58,870 --> 00:10:01,240
I can't even count the times
she's humiliated me.

165
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:03,770
If you don't do something about this,

166
00:10:04,040 --> 00:10:05,840
I feel like this stress
is going to kill me.

167
00:10:06,610 --> 00:10:10,310
How can anyone be so viciously abusive?

168
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:14,520
Exactly, Father...

169
00:10:14,520 --> 00:10:16,350
I mean, Chairman.

170
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:18,460
Go on, ask anyone on the street.

171
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:20,760
No matter how much she hates me,

172
00:10:21,060 --> 00:10:22,890
how could she grab
her mother-in-law by the hair...

173
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:26,060
and behave so disrespectfully?

174
00:10:26,530 --> 00:10:29,200
I was just so shocked.

175
00:10:29,870 --> 00:10:33,100
That was traumatizing...

176
00:10:33,570 --> 00:10:34,840
Yeom San Wol.

177
00:10:34,840 --> 00:10:35,910
Cut the act.

178
00:10:36,270 --> 00:10:37,610
And what about what you did?

179
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:47,590
My dear daughter-in-law.

180
00:10:49,190 --> 00:10:50,350
Apologize to me this instant.

181
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:54,460
- I will get an apology out of you.
- Apologize for what?

182
00:10:54,460 --> 00:10:55,760
Even without a formal ceremony,

183
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:59,260
part of your duty is
to help us all get along as a family.

184
00:10:59,930 --> 00:11:02,600
A peaceful home
makes for a prosperous business.

185
00:11:02,800 --> 00:11:03,800
Don't you forget that.

186
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:11,580
Now you're so powerful,

187
00:11:11,580 --> 00:11:14,050
so Mrs. Yeom and Team Leader Jin
are perfect to control you.

188
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:17,480
I had them stay in my house so that
they could keep an eye on you, CEO Chae.

189
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:18,850
It's the perfect setup.

190
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:25,790
What did you just say?

191
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:28,160
You're the one who found
this out, Baek Ho?

192
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:29,360
Yes.

193
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:31,830
So you found out why my dad went there?

194
00:11:32,060 --> 00:11:33,360
No, not exactly.

195
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,630
I found out that,
around the time of the accident,

196
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:39,440
a man bought a bottle of soju
from a nearby corner store.

197
00:11:40,070 --> 00:11:41,270
How did you find that out?

198
00:11:42,140 --> 00:11:44,140
I went to the scene myself
and did some digging.

199
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:47,950
So was it my dad who bought the soju
from that store?

200
00:11:48,080 --> 00:11:50,250
No, I showed them his photo,

201
00:11:50,510 --> 00:11:53,320
- and they said it was someone else.
- Then who was it?

202
00:11:54,150 --> 00:11:55,390
What did he look like?

203
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:57,720
I told the detective,

204
00:11:57,720 --> 00:11:59,160
and he suggested
we get a composite sketch made.

205
00:11:59,520 --> 00:12:01,530
Once we get the composite sketch,
we'll be able to find him in no time.

206
00:12:01,730 --> 00:12:04,860
It's possible he was drinking
with your father.

207
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:07,260
- That makes sense.
- Let go of me!

208
00:12:08,100 --> 00:12:09,270
Hey, get off me!

209
00:12:23,810 --> 00:12:26,320
So what if I killed someone?
Does that make me a monster?

210
00:12:28,990 --> 00:12:30,120
It's okay now, Jang Mi.

211
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:32,490
Okay, thanks.

212
00:12:42,330 --> 00:12:43,330
Here you go.

213
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:44,500
(Around 2:30 a.m. on January 15, 2026)

214
00:12:44,570 --> 00:12:45,900
(Looking for a man who bought soju
in Yeongseo-myeon vanished.)

215
00:12:46,800 --> 00:12:48,740
He looks kind of familiar,

216
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:52,110
but I also feel like
I've never seen him before.

217
00:12:52,380 --> 00:12:53,380
I see what you mean.

218
00:12:53,740 --> 00:12:56,780
I'll run his face
through the criminal database first.

219
00:12:57,250 --> 00:13:01,590
Right now, while there are some questions,
we have no evidence of foul play.

220
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:06,360
This case will most likely be closed
as a simple traffic accident.

221
00:13:06,690 --> 00:13:09,660
- The case will be closed?
- But what about all the inconsistencies?

222
00:13:10,090 --> 00:13:13,830
Most bereaved families react
the way you are.

223
00:13:14,100 --> 00:13:17,570
It's not easy to accept
that it was just a traffic accident.

224
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:18,840
But, Detective.

225
00:13:19,340 --> 00:13:23,110
My dad could have gotten into an accident
somewhere else and been moved.

226
00:13:23,170 --> 00:13:24,180
I don't know about that.

227
00:13:24,440 --> 00:13:27,040
Right now, there's no evidence
to suggest...

228
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:29,910
it was more than a traffic accident.

229
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,120
Hold on a second.

230
00:13:35,090 --> 00:13:37,350
- Hey, Tae Sook.
- Get over here and watch the store.

231
00:13:37,690 --> 00:13:40,930
I need to get a part-time job to pay off
the back rent. We can’t go on like this.

232
00:13:42,060 --> 00:13:43,060
Okay, I'll be right there.

233
00:13:53,570 --> 00:13:56,140
Your resume says you ran a side dish shop.

234
00:13:56,540 --> 00:13:58,840
Yes, I was helping my sister run it.

235
00:13:59,810 --> 00:14:02,650
But I'm very confident
in my cooking skills and customer service.

236
00:14:04,110 --> 00:14:07,750
Actually, we prioritize the freshness
of our ingredients over cooking skills.

237
00:14:08,090 --> 00:14:10,350
Our vegetables are always delivered
fresh every morning.

238
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:14,960
Since customers get their own pot,
hygiene is our number one priority.

239
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:18,830
Of course. I know that.
From working at the side dish shop,

240
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:22,700
I learned that I need fresh ingredients
to bring out the food's natural flavor.

241
00:14:23,370 --> 00:14:26,040
I came here with my dad and family
the other day to eat,

242
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:29,740
- and I was impressed by the hygiene.
- You noticed.

243
00:14:30,470 --> 00:14:33,680
I promise I'll work really hard.

244
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:36,880
I'll be meticulous about freshness
and maintaining hygiene.

245
00:14:37,650 --> 00:14:39,250
Please give me a chance.

246
00:14:40,080 --> 00:14:41,420
All right, then.

247
00:14:42,890 --> 00:14:43,890
Thank you.

248
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:53,360
- Mom!
- No!

249
00:14:54,130 --> 00:14:56,900
Mom, what's wrong?

250
00:14:57,940 --> 00:15:00,170
Jang Mi, that thing...

251
00:15:00,170 --> 00:15:01,770
It's scary. That thing!

252
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:05,210
- That's scary.
- What?

253
00:15:05,710 --> 00:15:07,440
What's scary about this?

254
00:15:09,980 --> 00:15:13,020
It's scary. Suk Hee is so scared.

255
00:15:16,150 --> 00:15:17,190
Wait.

256
00:15:17,920 --> 00:15:19,690
Mom, what's wrong?

257
00:15:19,690 --> 00:15:21,290
- Suk Hee?
- Mom.

258
00:15:21,590 --> 00:15:23,590
- Mom, what's wrong?
- What's wrong?

259
00:15:24,760 --> 00:15:25,760
Suk Hee?

260
00:15:26,830 --> 00:15:28,870
Go away!

261
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:34,070
Mom, what's wrong?

262
00:15:34,070 --> 00:15:35,070
I'm right here.

263
00:15:35,110 --> 00:15:36,470
Mom, calm down.

264
00:15:36,570 --> 00:15:38,280
He's scary.

265
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:39,280
Go away!

266
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:40,280
He's scaring me.

267
00:15:42,510 --> 00:15:44,550
(Case Summary, Yeongseo Police Chief)

268
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:48,190
Why are you scared of him?

269
00:15:48,250 --> 00:15:51,290
He's scary. Suk Hee is scared.

270
00:15:53,260 --> 00:15:54,290
That's weird.

271
00:15:55,790 --> 00:15:59,230
Now that I look at him,
he does kind of look like Manager Lee.

272
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,370
So, what does that mean?

273
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,200
At the time of Dad's accident,

274
00:16:04,640 --> 00:16:06,500
Manager Lee was the one
who bought soju at the corner store?

275
00:16:08,010 --> 00:16:10,110
No, that can't be right.

276
00:16:22,990 --> 00:16:25,720
Manager Lee works for CEO Chae.

277
00:16:26,220 --> 00:16:27,520
He's her loyal right-hand man.

278
00:16:28,790 --> 00:16:31,730
But then why does my mom keep saying
she's scared of Manager Lee?

279
00:16:33,030 --> 00:16:34,470
This is so weird.

280
00:16:37,470 --> 00:16:40,700
What? You're saying
Seo Rin's been digging into my past?

281
00:16:41,340 --> 00:16:42,370
Yes.

282
00:16:42,370 --> 00:16:44,170
When we went to the funeral home,

283
00:16:44,240 --> 00:16:46,040
Seo Rin's car was in the parking lot too.

284
00:16:46,540 --> 00:16:47,540
What?

285
00:16:48,010 --> 00:16:51,220
- Does that mean she was at the service?
- I haven't confirmed that.

286
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:55,020
One of my men saw her park her car
in the underground parking lot,

287
00:16:56,190 --> 00:16:57,220
but then he lost her.

288
00:16:57,550 --> 00:16:59,360
He only saw the car again
when it was leaving.

289
00:16:59,460 --> 00:17:03,260
Useless fools!
How would Seo Rin even know to go there?

290
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:05,200
That doesn't make any sense.

291
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:08,870
It's possible Seo Rin was the only one
who saw Oh Jang Mi the other day.

292
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:10,270
If that's the case,

293
00:17:10,730 --> 00:17:13,740
does that mean she's starting to suspect
she has a twin?

294
00:17:13,870 --> 00:17:15,610
If by any chance she overheard us,

295
00:17:16,710 --> 00:17:18,140
that would be a huge problem, wouldn't it?

296
00:17:18,710 --> 00:17:20,640
A huge problem is an understatement.

297
00:17:21,180 --> 00:17:24,980
Everything we've worked for
could go up in smoke.

298
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:28,750
We need to keep a close eye on Seo Rin.

299
00:17:29,790 --> 00:17:30,790
Understood.

300
00:17:31,890 --> 00:17:34,930
Getting her married to our Jun Ho
is the top priority right now.

301
00:17:35,930 --> 00:17:36,930
Right.

302
00:17:37,460 --> 00:17:39,130
Jun Ho has his interview today, right?

303
00:17:40,060 --> 00:17:41,130
Excellent.

304
00:17:45,500 --> 00:17:48,210
I like this shot. Right.

305
00:17:48,810 --> 00:17:50,310
- Let's get one more.
- One more shot.

306
00:17:50,370 --> 00:17:52,540
- Okay.
- Yes, that pose is great.

307
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:08,330
This is absolutely delicious.

308
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:11,060
It just melts in my mouth.

309
00:18:13,300 --> 00:18:18,000
So, you're the new general manager
of Food and Beverage for Dream Hotel,

310
00:18:18,240 --> 00:18:19,340
First off, congratulations.

311
00:18:20,200 --> 00:18:21,910
Could you start by sharing your thoughts
on the appointment?

312
00:18:22,170 --> 00:18:25,540
I think it'd be more fitting
to talk about my plans instead.

313
00:18:26,910 --> 00:18:30,050
Food and beverage at Dream Hotel
will no longer be just a service.

314
00:18:30,380 --> 00:18:33,180
It will become a brand
that represents our hotel.

315
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:36,550
Creating the top brand
in the hotel industry.

316
00:18:37,720 --> 00:18:39,060
That is my plan.

317
00:18:41,190 --> 00:18:44,930
- Here, come on and eat.
- No, I'm fine.

318
00:18:48,370 --> 00:18:50,830
How long are you going to keep moping
around like this?

319
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:55,410
Someone died because of me.
How could I possibly eat anything?

320
00:18:55,470 --> 00:18:56,910
So are you going to die, too?

321
00:18:58,340 --> 00:18:59,840
How many days has it been?

322
00:19:00,280 --> 00:19:02,680
You've only been drinking,
not eating a proper meal.

323
00:19:03,580 --> 00:19:05,250
Are you just going
to waste away and die, too?

324
00:19:06,850 --> 00:19:09,650
- Why would you say that?
- But it's true, isn't it?

325
00:19:10,650 --> 00:19:13,360
It's not like you hit him on purpose.

326
00:19:13,460 --> 00:19:14,630
Let's be honest.

327
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:17,230
It was just a case of bad luck
for both you and him.

328
00:19:18,260 --> 00:19:22,100
What's the use of torturing yourself
with guilt over it every day?

329
00:19:24,270 --> 00:19:26,740
I never should have gone out that day.

330
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:30,140
Because I deceived you
and had feelings for Hwa Young,

331
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,840
this is my punishment.

332
00:19:32,640 --> 00:19:37,550
I know you're a soft-hearted
and incredibly kind person.

333
00:19:37,950 --> 00:19:40,880
But it was an accident.
It couldn't be helped.

334
00:19:41,350 --> 00:19:42,420
Please, just stop.

335
00:19:43,090 --> 00:19:46,490
Just come back to your old self. Please?

336
00:19:46,860 --> 00:19:49,160
Honey, I'm sorry,

337
00:19:49,690 --> 00:19:52,900
but I still miss Hwa Young.

338
00:19:53,830 --> 00:19:54,830
Here.

339
00:19:56,170 --> 00:19:57,670
Try this. See if it's seasoned okay.

340
00:20:01,410 --> 00:20:02,410
Is it?

341
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,340
It's delicious.

342
00:20:31,840 --> 00:20:34,500
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

343
00:20:38,210 --> 00:20:40,210
(Suk Hee's Side Dishes)

344
00:20:42,350 --> 00:20:44,550
Oh my, we're not quite open yet,

345
00:20:44,550 --> 00:20:46,280
so we only have
some side dishes available.

346
00:20:46,880 --> 00:20:50,050
That's fine. Could you pack some up
for me, please?

347
00:20:51,220 --> 00:20:52,220
Sure.

348
00:21:03,570 --> 00:21:05,470
- My stomach!
- Excuse me?

349
00:21:05,540 --> 00:21:06,670
I'm so sorry.

350
00:21:07,670 --> 00:21:08,940
I'll come back another time.

351
00:21:14,950 --> 00:21:15,950
What just happened?

352
00:21:18,620 --> 00:21:19,620
My stomach...

353
00:21:39,700 --> 00:21:43,170
(Oh Jang Mi)

354
00:22:02,760 --> 00:22:04,630
I've seen some strange women,
but she takes the cake.

355
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:07,830
Why did she suddenly grab
my hair like that?

356
00:22:08,030 --> 00:22:09,930
- What happened, Auntie?
- What's wrong?

357
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,700
A pregnant customer came in...

358
00:22:11,700 --> 00:22:14,400
and grabbed my hair,
claiming her stomach hurt.

359
00:22:15,210 --> 00:22:16,310
She looked like she was in so much pain,

360
00:22:16,310 --> 00:22:17,670
I thought I should take her
to the hospital,

361
00:22:18,040 --> 00:22:20,840
- but before I knew it, she was gone.
- She must have been in a rush.

362
00:22:21,810 --> 00:22:24,350
Bo Ra, should we paint over here, too?

363
00:22:26,050 --> 00:22:29,320
You were looking for a part-time job.
How did it go?

364
00:22:29,620 --> 00:22:32,590
I think it went well.
She said she'll call me.

365
00:22:32,820 --> 00:22:35,660
I feel bad. I should be the one working.

366
00:22:35,890 --> 00:22:38,160
You just focus on working hard
at the shop from now on.

367
00:22:38,760 --> 00:22:42,570
Dad would've wanted us
to be strong and move on.

368
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:51,170
Don't tense up your shoulders.
Let your arms hang naturally.

369
00:22:51,240 --> 00:22:52,610
- Naturally.
- Right. And your wrists like this...

370
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:54,540
- Okay, lock it in. There.
- Locked in.

371
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:57,710
I’ll trust you
and give it a try, Chairman.

372
00:23:02,820 --> 00:23:06,990
- My gosh.
- That's just how golf is sometimes.

373
00:23:07,990 --> 00:23:09,960
It's because all I ever play
is virtual golf.

374
00:23:10,430 --> 00:23:11,960
I need to play on a real course
to get better.

375
00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:15,670
You're just getting in?

376
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:36,390
(Oh Jang Mi)

377
00:23:39,060 --> 00:23:42,530
(Chae Hwa Young)

378
00:23:46,430 --> 00:23:48,830
(Chae Hwa Young, Oh Jang Mi, Ma Seo Rin)

379
00:23:49,070 --> 00:23:50,070
Right.

380
00:23:50,870 --> 00:23:53,840
A DNA test will make everything clear.

381
00:24:03,610 --> 00:24:06,580
- What is it?
- Is that how you answer your mother?

382
00:24:07,080 --> 00:24:10,350
Seo Rin, you haven't been at the office.
What have you been doing?

383
00:24:10,950 --> 00:24:12,790
- Where are you now?
- Just around.

384
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:15,530
"Just around" where?
Why aren't you at the office?

385
00:24:15,990 --> 00:24:18,090
How do you expect to take over Dream
at this rate?

386
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:19,700
I'm asking, where are you now?

387
00:24:19,760 --> 00:24:22,600
Am I a little kid?
Do I have to report my every move to you?

388
00:24:22,900 --> 00:24:24,430
What's with the attitude?

389
00:24:25,740 --> 00:24:28,240
I bought a watch for Kang Jun Ho,
the one you’re so crazy about.

390
00:24:29,570 --> 00:24:32,940
So get to the office now
and stop goofing off.

391
00:24:33,010 --> 00:24:34,010
A watch?

392
00:24:34,810 --> 00:24:38,380
Okay. You always know just
what I want, Mom.

393
00:24:39,120 --> 00:24:40,120
Thank you.

394
00:24:46,260 --> 00:24:48,990
First, I need to drop this off.

395
00:25:01,670 --> 00:25:03,210
What makes you think you're welcome here?

396
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:05,040
I'm sorry, Tae Pyung.

397
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:09,050
I'll do whatever it takes
to make up for what my dad did.

398
00:25:09,980 --> 00:25:12,550
- So please, forgive him.
- And how are you supposed to do that?

399
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,120
How ridiculous.

400
00:25:20,220 --> 00:25:23,530
You haven't heard from the police,
have you?

401
00:25:24,360 --> 00:25:25,360
No.

402
00:25:26,560 --> 00:25:27,700
About what my father did,

403
00:25:28,670 --> 00:25:32,170
- I'm so sorry, Jang Mi.
- You don't have to keep apologizing.

404
00:25:32,700 --> 00:25:34,940
You're not the one
who caused my dad's accident.

405
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:37,470
I know, but I can't help
feeling responsible.

406
00:25:38,380 --> 00:25:41,210
That's why I've been looking
into your father's accident.

407
00:25:42,010 --> 00:25:44,450
I'm hoping it might help
answer some questions.

408
00:25:44,850 --> 00:25:48,820
- So, did you find anything?
- I went to the police station earlier...

409
00:25:49,250 --> 00:25:51,920
and re-examined the dashcam footage
from my father's car.

410
00:25:52,460 --> 00:25:53,890
Before the car hit him,

411
00:25:54,360 --> 00:25:57,190
your father was lying
in the middle of the road.

412
00:25:57,830 --> 00:26:00,160
But he was already bleeding from the head.

413
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:01,160
What?

414
00:26:01,670 --> 00:26:03,900
Then are you saying
someone attacked my dad?

415
00:26:04,070 --> 00:26:05,270
I'm not certain,

416
00:26:05,800 --> 00:26:07,240
but it's possible.

417
00:26:08,940 --> 00:26:10,640
None of this is adding up.

418
00:26:11,680 --> 00:26:14,080
I have to go to the accident scene
first thing tomorrow.

419
00:26:14,180 --> 00:26:18,050
- Don't go alone. Let's go together.
- And about that composite sketch,

420
00:26:18,420 --> 00:26:22,020
when my mom saw the sketch,
she screamed that he looked terrifying.

421
00:26:22,350 --> 00:26:26,690
- After seeing the sketch?
- Yes. It happened at our store,

422
00:26:26,860 --> 00:26:29,530
and also at the funeral home
when she saw Manager Lee.

423
00:26:30,290 --> 00:26:31,330
What if...

424
00:26:32,130 --> 00:26:34,760
the sketch is of Manager Lee?

425
00:26:35,170 --> 00:26:36,230
Manager Lee?

426
00:26:58,490 --> 00:27:00,120
(The First Man)

427
00:27:00,190 --> 00:27:03,060
I'm not my mother's daughter?
Then who am I?

428
00:27:03,430 --> 00:27:07,700
That woman is my mother?
No, this is all a huge mistake.

429
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:09,600
Doesn't he look like Manager Lee?

430
00:27:09,970 --> 00:27:13,870
How can the CCTV in a hotel this large
be down due to a malfunction?

431
00:27:13,970 --> 00:27:15,410
Things like that happen all the time.

432
00:27:15,570 --> 00:27:17,470
I have to use this to find out everything
about my mom.

433
00:27:17,870 --> 00:27:21,680
I hope my mom isn't a monster
who would try to kill Oh Jang Mi.

434
00:27:22,710 --> 00:27:24,710
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
